Text.Value: Wyll Ravengard? Lord Gortash said you might be stumbling this way.
Don't know what he needs you for when he's got those bloody great Steel Watchers.
I'm sure you will.
This is ridiculous. I already got permission to enter.
No entry today. Special occasion.
As you can see, I have an urgent dispatch for Duke Ravengard.
Hells - first Stelmane, and now this. Hurry up, then - last door on the right.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The guard tilts her head as if reading your documents. No reason to show the documents.

Text.Value: The joke's on you. No entry - that's the end of it.
Lower the gates - special permission!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: turns away from the player and calls out to unseen gatekeeper off-screen
EditorData.NodeContext: turns away from the player and calls out to unseen gatekeeper off-screen

Text.Value: But... unprecedented times and all that. Head through - you want the last door on your right.
Workshy minstrels, I swear to Helm - Whatever. I'm not getting it in the neck because some flautist was missing.
How many bodyguards does the man need? Get on, then - last door on the right.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The guard tilts her head as if reading your documents. No reason to show the documents.

Text.Value: Baldur's Gate is my home. I don't need permission to enter.
On with you, then.
What's so special about this occasion?
Special occasion. Wyrm's Rock is closed - invited guests only.
See this? I've been invited to the ordination.
Here you are, then.
Such a bother. What if I were to contribute to the 'Flaming Fist Orphans' Fund'?
Gortash's got all the protection he needs. A cultist makes so much as a peep, the Watch'll turn them to cinder.
Bah - the place is near to bursting with guards. The duke's safer than a snail in a steel shell.
Valeria? Well I'm not messing about with a murder inquiry, for damn sure.
Leave.
You want the last door on the right. Hop to it, bard - you're late enough as is.
Ah yes, the 'Orphans' Fund'. You can pay me directly - I'll make sure to pass your gold to the 'orphans'. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
Good try. But no.
Sorry, chum, can't let you through. Wyrm's Rock's closed for the day.
I am Lord Gortash's new occultist - let me pass or your name goes in the Book of Vile Darkness.
Gortash's got all the protection he needs. A cultist makes so much as a peep, the Fist'll turn them to cinder.
I'll see that the 'orphans' put your donation to good use.
I'm here to protect Archduke-Elect Gortash.
Not closed to Duke Ulder Ravengard's own son, surely?
What's special about today?
I'll shove your book somewhere vile and dark if you don't stop wasting my time.
Go on now. Entry granted.
I'll come back later.
An assassin is in pursuit of Duke Ravengard. I need to warn him!
Bah - the place is crawling with Watchers. The duke's safer than a snail in a steel shell.
I'll be - you don't look the posh sort. Last door on the right. Go on, make merry.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: The guard tilts her head as if reading your documents. No reason to show the documents.

Text.Value: Investigator Valeria needs me in the Lower City - a serial killer's on the loose.
It's not my job to coddle workshy, disorganised minstrels. It's your job to turn up on time with everyone else. Sod off.
Attack.
Straight ahead, across the bridge. A blind ogre couldn't miss it.
You having a laugh, devil-boy? I know Ravengard - and last I knew, his spawn wasn't sporting those horns.
Ordination is what. Lord Gortash is becoming Archduke. All the peers came to pay regards.

RollAdvantageReason.Value: Son of Grand Duke Ulder Ravengard

Please let me in - I'm meant to be in the coronation orchestra, it's my big break!
Provide the pass you took from Valeria.
Not closed to Duke Ulder Ravengard's own son, surely?
Looks in order. Last door on the right. Don't keep the Duke waiting.
